Package C2G8_Project

Class PassengerRequest

java.lang.Object
C2G8_Project.PassengerRequest
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<PassengerRequest>
final class PassengerRequest extends Object implements Serializable, Comparable<PassengerRequest>
Class represents a record for a passenger request within the scenario. Class static methods contain factory to create scenario with given duration and number of people.
Author:
Jayson Mendoza

  • Method Details

    • loadScenario

      public static ArrayList<PassengerRequest> loadScenario() throws IncompatableInputFile
      Load a scenario by first fetching the default file. If the file is not present this will print warnings in the log and then save then load a newly generated scenario. If the file existed but was corrupted a warning will print advising the deletion of the file along with possible causes and then a new scenario will be generated and loaded but the file will not be replaced.
      Returns:
      Throws:
      IncompatableInputFile

    • generateScenario

      public static ArrayList<PassengerRequest> generateScenario(int numPeople, long scenarioDurationMills) throws IncompatableInputFile
      Generates a scenario that spans a given duration and includes a number of passengers
      Parameters:
      numPeople - The number of passengers throughout the scenario
      scenarioDurationMills - The duration of the scenario in Milliseconds
      Returns:
      A sorted list of PassengerRequests
      Throws:
      IncompatableInputFile
